# Pin LF ONLY for files that break when checked out with CRLF on Windows. This is
# deliberately narrow — no repo-wide `* text=auto` renormalization — so it changes
# exactly these file types and nothing else.
#
#  - gradlew       : Linux shells reject a CRLF shebang (/bin/sh^M).
#  - *.sh          : same, for infra/ init + migration helper scripts.
#  - db migrations : Flyway checksums the file bytes; CRLF != the LF the DB was
#                    migrated with -> "checksum mismatch" against a restored DB.
gradlew   text eol=lf
*.sh      text eol=lf
*.sql     text eol=lf
